findings.suggestedFix:
Use a ref flag to prevent double-firing, or restructure: move the guard into the effect itself. Simplest fix:
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setTimeout(() => {
    setFadeOut(true);
    sessionStorage.setItem(SPLASH_KEY, '1');
    setTimeout(onDone, 600);
  }, 8000);
  return () => clearTimeout(timer);
}, [onDone]);
```
And in handleComplete use a ref guard instead of reading state:
```tsx
const doneRef = useRef(false);
const handleComplete = () => {
  if (doneRef.current) return;
  doneRef.current = true;
  setFadeOut(true);
  sessionStorage.setItem(SPLASH_KEY, '1');
  setTimeout(onDone, 600);
};
```

